762.question: How large are the improvements of the Attention-Sum Reader model when using the BookTest dataset?
762.response: {'Answer': 'The improvements of the Attention-Sum Reader model when using the BookTest dataset for named entity tasks are from a single model accuracy of 68.6% to 76.2%, and for a greedy ensemble from 71.0% to 78.4%. For common noun tasks, the improvement goes from a single model accuracy of 63.4% to 80.8%, and for a greedy ensemble from 67.5% to 83.7%.'}
762.answer: Answer with content missing: (Table 2) Accuracy of best AS reader results including ensembles are 78.4 and 83.7 when trained on BookTest compared to 71.0 and 68.9 when trained on CBT for Named endity and Common noun respectively.
